This paper is about the optimization of neural networks, which is a core topic in machine learning. The paper discusses the limitations of the Adam optimizer, which is a widely used adaptive optimizer for training neural networks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
